"=========================================
" Task 2: Process / Service Management
" Scenario: A critical service has stopped
"=========================================

"-----------------------------------------
" 1. Check if the service is running
"-----------------------------------------
# Use systemctl to check status
:!systemctl status nginx

# Use ps to confirm process
:!ps aux | grep nginx

"-----------------------------------------
" 2. Restart the service
"-----------------------------------------
:!sudo systemctl restart nginx

"-----------------------------------------
" 3. Verify service status after restart
"-----------------------------------------
:!systemctl status nginx

"-----------------------------------------
" 4. Check logs if service fails again
"-----------------------------------------
:!journalctl -u nginx -n 50

"-----------------------------------------
" 5. Verify service is listening (optional)
"-----------------------------------------
:!ss -tulnp | grep nginx

"-----------------------------------------
" 6. Enable service on reboot
"-----------------------------------------
:!sudo systemctl enable nginx

"-----------------------------------------
" Notes:
" - nginx is example, replace with actual service
" - ps aux | grep <service> helps check process
" - journalctl shows why service failed
" - Useful for production troubleshooting

